      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top with the <strong>remaining pastry square<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>,<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>pinch the edges of the pastry together and roll over tightly to form a border around the camembert</p><p>Score the <strong>pastry</strong> with a knife in a spiral shape, working from the centre outwards</p><p>Add the<strong> green beans </strong>with a sprinkle of <strong>water</strong> to the other side of the tray (or a separate one!) and cover with <strong>tin foil</strong>, then put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for 15-17 min or until the pastry is puffed up, golden and cooked through – this is your <strong>baked camembert pithivier & roasted green beans</strong></p>",
